# Auto-sync conflict avoidance for high-churn shared state (T-SYNC-07).
# active-checkouts.json: two machines bump fenceCounter/updatedAt every ~5 min; a plain
# 3-way merge conflicts every tick and the daemon diverges. Resolve by fenceCounter via
# a custom driver (scripts/merge-lease-state.sh, registered by openclaw-git-sync.sh).
docs/process/state/active-checkouts.json merge=leasestate
# task-queue.md is append-mostly from multiple machines; union keeps both sides rather
# than blocking the unattended daemon on an append/append overlap.
docs/process/task-queue.md merge=union
# tasks.json + task-counter.json: both machines mutate governed task state every session;
# a plain 3-way merge conflicts on the same task objects / counter and stalls the daemon
# (the #147 outage). Resolve deterministically via scripts/merge-taskstate.py: union tasks
# by taskId keeping the higher revision, counter = max(lastAssigned). Registered by
# openclaw-git-sync.sh alongside the leasestate driver.
docs/process/state/tasks.json merge=taskstate
docs/process/state/task-counter.json merge=taskstate
docs/process/state/tasks-archive.json merge=taskstate
# health-checks.json: high-churn self-heal state both machines rewrite (per-check `added`
# stamps, top-level updatedAt, ordering). It was the one governed-state file WITHOUT a driver,
# so every cross-machine pull aborted on it and local main diverged unboundedly (#437
# sync-integrity, 2026-06-22). Resolve via scripts/merge-healthchecks.py: union checks[] by
# name keeping newer `added`, union gaps, updatedAt = newer. Registered by openclaw-git-sync.sh.
docs/process/state/health-checks.json merge=healthchecks
# file-claims.jsonl: proactive cross-session source-edit claims (#308). Both machines
# APPEND claims; union keeps both sides so no live claim is dropped in a merge (the
# leasestate driver would copy one side wholesale and lose the peer's claims). Expired
# lines are filtered on read + swept by `file-claims.py prune`.
docs/process/state/file-claims.jsonl merge=union
# Append-only JSONL ledgers (one record per line, written from multiple sessions/machines):
# union keeps both sides so no appended row is clobbered when a merge overlaps. eval-corpus.jsonl
# is the agent-output evaluation corpus (PLAN-eval-pipeline.md); pr-ledger.jsonl is the merged-PR
# work ledger (#286). Both are append-only — never edited in place — so union is always safe.
docs/process/state/eval-corpus.jsonl merge=union
docs/process/state/pr-ledger.jsonl merge=union
# cloud-sessions.jsonl: ephemeral cloud/web sessions self-register here (append-only,
# one row per start/heartbeat/end) so Hearth's dashboard can surface them in the
# Sessions panel — the repo is the only medium the ephemeral container and Hearth share.
# Written from many parallel cloud sessions; union keeps every row on a merge.
docs/process/state/cloud-sessions.jsonl merge=union
Hearth/state/gpu-oom-incidents.jsonl merge=union
# voice-deltas.jsonl: Writing studio appends one row per meaningful edit-session
# (#8, before->after body diff) so writing-voice-synthesize.py can propose voice-
# profile deltas. Append-only, may be written from either machine — union keeps
# every captured edit on a merge.
projects/writing/voice-deltas.jsonl merge=union
Hearth/memory/mindset-ledger.jsonl merge=union
